subSubSection.paragraph:
The status of 

Gabbia

has been variously interpreted. It has been given generic status (
Tryon, 1865
; 
Cotton, 1942
; 
Iredale, 1943
, 
1944
; 
Smith, 1992
) or treated as a subgenus of 

Bithynia

(or 

Bulimus

) (
Tryon, 1883
; 
Thiele, 1929
; 
Wenz, 1938
; 
Starmühlner, 1976
), while others (
Tate, 1882
; 
Hedley, 1896
; 
Smith, 1887
; 
Pace, 1973
) have treated it as a synonym of 

Bithynia

. 

Gabbia

has also been used for some SE Asian taxa, either as a genus (e.g. 
Habe, 1964
; 
Benthem Jutting, 1963
; 
Chung, 1984
; 
Chitramvong & Upatham, 1989
; 
Chitramvong, 1991
, 
1992
) or subgenus of 

Bithynia

(
Kuroda, 1941
; 
Brandt, 1968
, 
1974
).
